To identify unnecessary re-renders, I used React DevTools Profiler and browser developer tools.

First, I opened the React DevTools Profiler and recorded interactions while using the application. This helped me see which components were re-rendering frequently and how long each render was taking.

I also used techniques like console logging inside components to quickly confirm when a component was re-rendering during development.

After identifying unnecessary renders, I optimized them by:

Using React.memo to prevent re-rendering when props didn’t change

Memoizing functions with useCallback

Memoizing computed values with useMemo

Avoiding unnecessary state updates

Splitting large components into smaller components

After applying these optimizations, I verified the improvements again using the React Profiler, which showed fewer renders and better rendering time.

Shorter Version (if they interrupt)

